entries.description: Courtney Pettifor, 28, was banned permanently from teaching after he sent thousands of inappropriate messages to female pupils at Witchford Village College, near Ely in Cambridgeshire.

entries.title: Dr Richard Freeman's High Court appeal fails and he will now face a UK Anti-Doping investigation
entries.description: MIKE KEEGAN: After the appeal was dismissed, the probe will now restart, with Freeman facing a minimum four-year ban. He could potentially be stopped from working in sport for life.

entries.title: How ship carrying more than 900 Jewish refugees from Nazis in WWII was turned away from Cuba and US
entries.description: The MS St. Louis, a luxury cruise liner, was carrying Jewish men, women and children fleeing oppression in Nazi Germany when it was turned away from Cuba in May 1939. Above: Passengers on the ship.

entries.title: Tasmanian boarding house for homeless and children live in horror conditions in New Town, Hobart
entries.description: Flint House is a privately-owned crisis boarding house in Hobart's north where vulnerable residents of all ages pay up to $450 a fortnight for a roof over their heads.

entries.title: Teacher loses discrimination case after suing school for failing to stop pupils racially abusing her
entries.description: Rizwana Mallet-Ali tried to sue Bertha Park High School in Perth, Scotland, after claiming bosses at the secondary failed to stop pupils from racially abusing her in class.

entries.title: 'The Three Tenors' opera star Placido Domingo faces new sexual harassment claims from Spanish singer
entries.description: Spanish opera singer Plácido Domingo, known as one of The Three Tenors, faced a new allegation of sexual harassment on Sunday during an interview on Spanish television.

entries.title: MPs to vote TONIGHT on new strikes laws as Labour blasted for 'putting lives at risk'
entries.description: Rishi Sunak wants to give ministers the power to impose minimum service levels in key public services - such as the NHS, schools and transport networks - during walkouts by unions.

entries.title: Daughter, 21, accused of stabbing her dinner lady mother, 58, more than 30 times
entries.description: A daughter accused of stabbing her dinner lady mother to death more than 30 times and filming the bloody aftermath on her phone has admitted to killing her - but denies murder.

entries.title: Thousands of teachers could strike despite warnings - as Scottish union members walk out
entries.description: Leaders of the National Education Union (NEU) are expected to reveal today if teachers across the country will launch strike action after balloting its 300,000 members.

entries.title: Father jailed for killing wife is FREED after almost 25 years
entries.description: Thomas Rhodes, 63, was convicted in 1998 of first- and second-degree murder in the death of his 36-year-old wife Jane Rhodes, who fell overboard and drowned on a night-time boat ride.

entries.title: Underground bunker allegedly used for growing cannabis raided by police in Adelaide
entries.description: Officers attended a semi-rural property in the suburb of Coromandel East on Monday, where they discovered the bunker's entrance.

entries.title: British gardens have seen the greatest explosion of winter colour in more than a DECADE
entries.description: British gardens have seen the greatest explosion of winter colour in more than a decade due to the topsy-turvy weather, according to the Royal Horticultural Society.

entries.title: 'It wouldn't fill a five-year-old!': Frustrated mother shares photo of 'tiny' school lunch portions
entries.description: Leanne Pengelly, 43, snapped a picture of the free school meal provided at Millbrook Primary School in Newport - showing a meal of cabbage, potatoes and carrots with some gravy.

entries.description: Britain said on Saturday it would send 14 of its Challenger 2 main battle tanks to Ukraine as well as other advanced artillery support in the coming weeks.

entries.title: Tory minister Penny Mordaunt slams the Church of England over gay marriage ban
entries.description: Penny Mordaunt, who ran to become party leader and prime minister twice last year, accused religious authorities of treating LGBT people as 'second-class citizens'.

entries.title: Woman's body found in Penrith unit in Sydney as police also find her car burnt out nearby
entries.description: A woman's body has been found in a unit and her car later discovered burnt out in bushland an hour's drive away leading to a full scale police investigation.

entries.title: Social media users react to 'Blue Monday' dubbed the 'most depressing day of the year'
entries.description: January 16 has been dubbed the 'most depressing day of the year'. Blue Monday was coined by psychologist Dr Cliff Arnall, who worked out a formula for the third Monday in January.

entries.description: David Carrick worked for the Met Police as a firearms officer based at the Houses of Parliament in London.

entries.title: Cash-strapped council's £2,000 King Charles mural is mocked by locals
entries.description: A local authority has been ridiculed for spending nearly £2,000 on a mural of King Charles III which has been likened to a Spitting Image puppet.

entries.title: Stalker used Alexa to spy on ex-lover before threatening to stab her and throw acid is spared jail
entries.description: Hassan Mehmet, 35, waged a campaign of harassment against Shelby Laidlaw, warning he would pull her teeth out after he deliberately crashed her Jaguar in a motorway suicide attempt.

entries.title: Pope fuels rumours he may quit in sermon on 'the virtue of stepping aside at the right time'
entries.description: Pope Francis fuelled speculation he might renounce his position after reflecting on knowing when to step aside from a role at the right moment in the Sunday Angelus address in Vatican City.

entries.title: Spider bite lands New Zealand pregnant mum in hospital for surgery and skin grafts: Renee Peck

entries.title: Boy racer, 19, who mowed down and killed mother  jailed for three years and eight months
entries.description: Lewis Clark (pictured), pleaded guilty to causing death by dangerous driving at Bournemouth Crown Court. He was jailed for three years and eight months.

entries.title: Cadbury launches range of new 91 calorie chocolate bars... so how do they compare to YOUR favourite?
entries.description: Cadbury has launched a new low-calorie offering in select supermarkets across the UK, which cost £1.25 for a box of five, and are filled with nougat and caramel and are coated in chocolate.

entries.title: Is this the ghost of a soldier? Creepy video of 'completely see-through man sitting on a bench'
entries.description: Josh Newton and George Moore, both 21, were driving through Northam, North Devon on the evening of December 28 when they captured what they say was a 'completely see-through man'.

entries.description: In 2011, the then-16-year-old said in an online forum that he felt 'nothing' when he looked at his family and his mind was 'blank'.

entries.title: UK and EU hold talks TODAY as efforts ramp up to end Northern Ireland Protocol row
entries.description: James Cleverly will speak with European Commission vice-president Maros Sefcovic via video link to discuss progress on ending the dispute over post-Brexit trade rules.

entries.title: Amazon delivery driver's fingertip is left in letterbox after it ripped off as he posted a parcel
entries.description: WARNING GRAPHIC CONTENT: Amazon driver Gareth Thompson, 40, from Plymouth, Devon, lost the tip of his finger after it became jammed inside a letterbox while delivering a parcel.

entries.title: Russia produces first batch of nuclear-armed Poseidon torpedo drones
entries.description: Pro-War fanatic Lt-Gen Andrey Gurulev claimed on Rossiya 1 channel that the deployment of British and German tanks to Ukraine was 'to kill us', and therefore was crossing a red line.

entries.title: Keir Starmer opposes Rishi Sunak's plan to widen police crackdown on road-blocking eco-protesters

entries.description: Tom Bower, who wrote an unauthorised biography of the Duchess of Sussex, suggested it would be naive for King Charles to seek a 'peace summit' with the Sussexes.

entries.title: WA town of Exmouth gets ready for thousands of visitors as best place to see total solar eclipse
entries.description: The path of totality will graze the tip of Western Australia in a 40-kilometre wide track near Exmouth and become the most accessible land-based place on Earth to view the 62 second spectacle.

entries.title: Australia weather: Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth: Cyclone and rain forcast

entries.title: Australians slam driver for 'illegal and disgusting' act with two dogs tethered to the back of a ute
entries.description: Australians are slamming a driver for tethering their two dogs on the back of their ute's open metal tray without the correct restraints and shelter as temperatures soared above 35C.

entries.description: Doctors and health experts rounded on Keir Starmer's plans for NHS reforms. Patients would face a worse NHS crisis it was said, after Labour proposed self-referrals for medical care.

entries.title: Man arrested on suspicion of attempted murder after drive-by shooting outside memorial service

entries.title: Molly Russell's father: Social media giants are failing to change to protect vulnerable children
entries.description: Social media giants have failed to make meaningful changes since the Molly Russell inquest, the teenager's father said last night.

entries.title: Eshays arrested over alleged Maserati and Jeep theft from Woodside Petroleum's Meg O'Neill in Perth

entries.title: New law should stop union barons from putting 'lives at immediate risk', Health Secretary says

entries.title: Human skeleton is found in abandoned building at UC Berkeley that hasn't been used for 'many years'

entries.title: Puppy dies from eating common garden plant in Australia
